{"body": "ActionDispatch already knows quite a bit about routes, formatting them to be human readable doesn't seem like too far of a leap. \n\nOn the perf side it looks like DebugExceptions is in the middleware in production, but the custom error pages are ignored unless `env['action_dispatch.show_detailed_exceptions']` is set. Restrict any route formatting/rendering code to within that section and there won't be any performance degradation. ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6252395", "created_at": "2012-06-11T18:40:55Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6696#issuecomment-6252395", "updated_at": "2012-06-11T18:40:55Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6696, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/schneems", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6ef42a6eab211ddd71ac423a80b42d15.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/received_events", "gravatar_id": "db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "schneems", "type": "User", "id": 59744, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523e305cbd354364b900e3bb"}, "id": 6252395, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6696"}
